@node intro "Introduction"

NSA-Patch is based around an old program I wrote to get AMOS programs to
multi-task with each other...

Since I already had patching routines, I decided to have a go at writing
a patcher to make things run faster...

What this program does is scan a program for any slow maths commands and
replaces them with MUCH faster ones!

Some programs work up to 4 TIMES faster after being patched!!!!!

Just as a quick example:

Worms:DC	- 42 Speed hits!
Photogenics	- 1,254 Speed Hits!


@endnode
@node sysreq "System Requirements"

Only the basics are needed to run this proggy !

Any Amiga with OS2.04+ and enough memory to hold the exe file to patch.

You also need reqtools.library in LIBS: , this isn't included with this 
archive as everyone should have a copy of it by now anyway!

@endnode
@node inst "Installation"

The easy bit :^)... 

Just copy the NSA-Patch.exe file to C:

Or wherever you want to install it really :)

I decided not to use a installer script cos it's only 1 file :)

Even a PC user could manage it :)


If any of you are wondering why I added a .exe to the end of the file name
then it's because several viri do not infect any file that has a . in the 
name!

This file has been check with VT v2.98 & VirusZ II v1.39.

@endnode

@node inuse "Using NSA-Patch"

NSA-Patch is a CLI ONLY Proggy...

If started from the CLI, it takes 1 filename to patch.

eg..  NSA-Patch.exe Myfile

If you've started it from the the CLI without a filename then it'll bring 
up a multi-select file requester so you can choose which files you want to 
patch :)

Selecting a directory & clicking on `All' is probably what most people will
use!

After you've given it a list of files to patch, you'll see a Scanning 
message, this is where it checks to see if the file is an amos executable!
AMOS Files can't be speed patched for some reason...

You'll then see a progress bar when it's actually patching for real :)

If the file is a compiled AMOS one, it'll remove the task switching code
from it, so it CAN'T tell any amos programs in memory to lock up!

If the program isn't an AMOS file, then it'll hunt down any slow maths 
commands to try and speed them up! :)

Please note: A minority of files just don't like being patched!..  NSA-Patch
has been designed to recognise some of them, but always make sure you have
backups of your files!

When finished, NSA-Patch creates a log of it's actions in RAM:NSA-Patch.log
so you can double check what it did...



What files Can I Patch?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Any Amiga executable program!!!..  Also you can patch libraries & devices
too :)


What Can't I Patch?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Any files with AMOS in the filename, Assembler & dissassembler files,
non-exe files (Obviously).


This patcher has been completely tested!!!!

I've patched EVERY exe file on my HD and it's still working :)


I think that's about it now :)

(Read the credz & greetz :) )


@endnode

